# SEO – Dubai Real Estate

- **Semantic HTML**: Use `<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<footer>` and one `<h1>` per page.
- **Headings**: Single `<h1>` per page (e.g. hero or main section title). Use `<h2>`–`<h6>` in logical order; no skipping levels.
- **Images**: Always set descriptive `alt` (e.g. "Luxury villa in Dubai Marina") and `width`/`height` where possible. Use `loading="lazy"` for below-the-fold images.
- **Links**: Use meaningful anchor text (avoid "click here"). Internal links use relative or root-relative paths; external use `rel="noopener noreferrer"` when opening in new tab.
- **Performance**: Prefer WebP for images; keep critical content above the fold; avoid blocking scripts in `<head>`.
- **Local / Dubai**: Include Dubai/UAE in titles and meta where relevant. Keep `index.html` meta (title, description, canonical, Open Graph) aligned with the live domain and content.
